val itemsDF = sqlContext.read.format("json")
  .load("file:/root/pipeline/html/advancedspark.com/json/software.json")
  .select($"id", $"title", $"category", $"description")

result.msg: itemsDF: org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame = [id: bigint, title: string, category: string, description: string]

id	title	category	description	words
1	Apache Cassandra	Database	The Apache Cassandra database is the right choice when you need scalability and high availability without compromising performance. Linear scalability and proven fault-tolerance on commodity hardware or cloud infrastructure make it the perfect platform for mission-critical data. Cassandra's support for replicating across multiple datacenters is best-in-class, providing lower latency for your users and the peace of mind of knowing that you can survive regional outages.  Cassandra's data model offers the convenience of column indexes with the performance of log-structured updates, strong support for denormalization and materialized views, and powerful built-in caching. 62	Spark Streaming	Library	Spark Streaming is an extension of the core Spark API that enables scalable, high-throughput, fault-tolerant stream processing of live data streams. // Split each document into words
val coreNLPLemmatizer = new CoreNLP()
  .setInputCol(stopWordsFilter.getOutputCol)
  .setOutputCol("lemmaWords")
  .setAnnotators(Array("lemma"))
  .setFlattenNestedFields(Array("sentence_token_lemma"))
  
//z.show(coreNLPLemmatizer.transform(itemsDF))

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.Word2Vec

val word2Vec = new Word2Vec()
  .setInputCol(coreNLPLemmatizer.getOutputCol)
  .setOutputCol("word2VecFeatures")
//  .setVectorSize(300)

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler

// Combine IDF and 
val featureVectorAssembler = new VectorAssembler()
  .setInputCols(Array(idf.getOutputCol, word2Vec.getOutputCol))
  .setOutputCol("allFeatures")

import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.StringIndexer

// Assign an Index to Each Category 
val categoryIndexer = new StringIndexer()
  .setInputCol("category")
  .setOutputCol("indexedCategory")

import org.apache.spark.ml.Pipeline

val pipeline = new Pipeline()
  .setStages(Array(coreNLPTokenizer, stopWordsFilter, coreNLPLemmatizer, tf, idf, word2Vec, featureVectorAssembler, categoryIndexer, classifier))

import org.apache.spark.ml.evaluation.MulticlassClassificationEvaluator

val metricName = "f1"

val modelEvaluator = new MulticlassClassificationEvaluator()
  .setLabelCol(classifier.getLabelCol)
  .setPredictionCol(classifier.getPredictionCol)
  .setMetricName(metricName)

import org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.ParamGridBuilder

val paramGrid = new ParamGridBuilder()
  .addGrid(tf.numFeatures, Array(10, 100, 1000))
  .addGrid(idf.minDocFreq, Array(1, 5, 10))
  .addGrid(word2Vec.vectorSize, Array(200, 300, 400))
  .addGrid(classifier.maxDepth, Array(1, 5, 10))
  .build()

import org.apache.spark.ml.tuning.CrossValidator

// K-Folds Cross Validation Combined With Param Grid 
val modelValidator = new CrossValidator()
  .setEstimator(pipeline)
  .setEvaluator(modelEvaluator)
  .setEstimatorParamMaps(paramGrid)
  .setNumFolds(5)
val bestModel = modelValidator.fit(itemsDF)
